review_text: I have no desire to slam a game that tells you to "nod" to go faster. It is probably for 1%-ers who have the money for esoteric devices, new jobbers without budgets, or well-to-do grandmothers that buy anything for the grandkids. (Even if you can buy them for $10 on whatever site--I'm unemployed, handicapped, and old...a real trifecta of poor.) I can't wait for someone to take my comments out of context. I believe everyone that says that it's a great game. Too bad they didn't aim it at the greater population of poor game players with phones and tablets. I suspect many of the "5,000" that downloaded this game just wanted to check it out like I did...not just assume that gear meant the name of a phone. This game gives you a double field of vision as if you were watching it with 3-D glasses, complete with the red and green swirlies on both fields of vision. I also would be willing to bet that any 3-D glasses would work; however, you wouldn't have access to the "nod" control...or any controls. Luck be with you GoDark!

I've seen some people say they try to cram too much into the game but I think they've found a fairly decent balance in the aspects they chose to incorporate.
